-- Rupee Climbs to Two-Year High, Supported by Strengthening Stock Inflows
-- B y   J a m e s   R e g a n
-- 2010-10-07T06:58:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/rupee-climbs-to-two-year-high-supported-by-strengthening-stock-inflows.html
India’s rupee rose to its strongest
level in more than two years, supported by increasing overseas
demand for the nation’s shares.  The currency climbed 0.8 percent to 44.183 per dollar as of
12:25 p.m. in Mumbai, contributing to a 6 percent advance for
the past month. It earlier touched 44.115, the strongest level
since Sept. 1, 2008.  Overseas investors have plowed more than $20 billion into
the nation’s shares this year and added to their holdings every
day from Aug. 27 through Oct.5, exchange data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Regan in Hong Kong at 
